<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREF.5B.5BMartin_Porter.5D.5D2009"><a href="/wiki/Martin_Porter" title="Martin Porter">Martin Porter</a> (2002). <a href="http://tartarus.org/~martin/essays/burkequote2.html" class="external text" title="http://tartarus.org/~martin/essays/burkequote2.html" rel="nofollow">"Four principles of quotation"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://tartarus.org/~martin/essays/burkequote2.html" class="external free" title="http://tartarus.org/~martin/essays/burkequote2.html" rel="nofollow">http://tartarus.org/~martin/essays/burkequote2.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-06-21</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Four+principles+of+quotation&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BMartin+Porter%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BMartin+Porter%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ftartarus.org%2F%7Emartin%2Fessays%2Fburkequote2.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edmund_Burke"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
